"If you leave a pen tester and a vulnerability assessment provider in a room together, there are bound to be fireworks. Because so few people offer both and much of the terminology is common to both but with different meanings, debates between the two sides can get heated. VA vendors on the one hand say that automatic is the way to go. Pen testers on the other hand come back with the argument that an automated assessment can never have the same rigour as one carried out by an expert."
